This paper focuses on optimizing network performance through joint design of traffic engineering and caching strategies in the context of Named Data Networking (NDN) architecture. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) category. Additionally, the paper discusses load balancing, forwarding, and caching, which are also relevant to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) categories. The paper also presents a framework for optimizing network performance, which could be relevant to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) category. Finally, the paper discusses the security implications of caching, which could be relevant to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) category.
